pkg-config
===========================================================
A utility used to retrieve information about installed libraries

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.0-45

Build requirements (these, or newer):
  cygwin-1.5.25-15
  gcc-3.4.4-999
  cygport-0.9.5-1
  binutils-20080624-2
  perl
  autoconf2.5
  automake1.7
  automake1.10 (yes, both versions)
  libtool
  bzr

Canonical homepage:
  http://pkgconfig.freedesktop.org/wiki/

Canonical download:
  http://pkgconfig.freedesktop.org/releases/

License:
  GPL

Language:
  C

===========================================================

Build instructions:
  unpack pkg-config-0.23b-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be unpacked
    under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./pkg-config-0.23b-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/pkg-config-0.23b-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/pkg-config-0.23b-X-src.tar.bz2

Or use './pkg-config-0.23b-X.sh prep' to get a patched source directory

To find out the files included in the binary distribution, you can
use "cygcheck -l pkg-config", or browse the listing for the appropriate 
version at <http://cygwin.com/packages/>.

